1) cd fluffos-2.9-ds2.04
2) ./configure skylib
3) make
4) make install
5) cd ../bin
6) vi config

Change the following:

name
mudlib directory
binary directory
external_port_1

7) ./driver ./config &
8) telnet localhost 8000

or whatever the port number is you specified

9) Follow the instruction in the file called README starting
at number 2.


A note on databases:
The original Skylib 1.8 assumed you had a database going.
This bundle does not make that assumption. To use your
computer's database, modify fluffos-2.9-ds2.02/local_options
to enable the DB package, and please know what you are
doing if you choose to try this. 
